[{"question":"This is a pretty big scandal, isn\u0027t it, Douglas Brinkley?","answer":"Well, yes it is.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":57,"aSentId":58},{"question":"Should it make much difference?","answer":"It\u0027s not going to make -- no, it\u0027s not going to make a whole lot of difference.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":79,"aSentId":80},{"question":"Is it that serious?","answer":"Well, we have to keep the word \"allegations\" out there right now.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":96,"aSentId":97},{"question":"Meredith, how are you?","answer":"I\u0027m good.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":137,"aSentId":138},{"question":"Why is it?","answer":"No, I\u0027m serious.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":146,"aSentId":147},{"question":"Shall we move off this rather uncomfortable subject?","answer":"Yes, we should.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":156,"aSentId":157},{"question":"Yes?","answer":"Because I reckon you\u0027d have a pretty good view of this.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":162,"aSentId":163},{"question":"Which is harder?","answer":"I think probably raising your children is the hardest thing you can do and the most rewarding, obviously, because you are -- you are shaping lives, you know.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":165,"aSentId":166},{"question":"What did you make of the row with Ann Romney, then, because it did seem a very strange battleground for any senior Democrats to pick?","answer":"Yes, you know, I\u0027m going to stick up a little bit for Hilary here.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":169,"aSentId":170},{"question":"When you see something like that, what -- what do you make of it?","answer":"I -- I\u0027m surprised she\u0027s not drunk every day.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":183,"aSentId":184},{"question":"Do you think America is ready for its first female president?","answer":"Yes, I do, Piers.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":191,"aSentId":192},{"question":"I want to talk to you about what you think of \"The Today Show\" losing its crown against \"GMA\" without you, obviously?","answer":"I\u0027m leaving.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":208,"aSentId":209},{"question":"What\u0027s going on?","answer":"It wasn\u0027t a miniskirt.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":225,"aSentId":226},{"question":"Where were you, Meredith, when you first heard of the Lauer deal?","answer":"I was heading toward the bathroom.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":245,"aSentId":246},{"question":"Reunite the -- the dream team?","answer":"No.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":276,"aSentId":277},{"question":"What -- what do you think of that?","answer":"Well, I hope that Ann has enough perspective, and I\u0027m sure that she does, to ignore it.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":305,"aSentId":306},{"question":"-- somebody like Sarah Palin, a rather divisive politician, to be, effectively, a \"Today Show\" host?","answer":"Yes, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":341,"aSentId":342},{"question":"So we should take this seriously, presumably?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":370,"aSentId":371},{"question":"When you saw this story, what gave you the desire to make a -- a film about it?","answer":"Well, Angelo Guglielmo, who is the producer, he brought us sort of a demo reel or, for lack of a better term, to show us what he was working on.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":388,"aSentId":389},{"question":"I mean it was a real -- it\u0027s a (INAUDIBLE) of a -- a weird thriller, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":403,"aSentId":404},{"question":"Because, in the end, if she was a comfort to them, how much does it really matter that she actually invented her own story?","answer":"It does in the sense that, yes, she was a comfort but it was also a terrible betrayal.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":436,"aSentId":437},{"question":"I mean, there\u0027s no stopping you, is there?","answer":"I plan to take over the -- in fact, your show is the next thing I plan to control.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"What are you doing there?","answer":"Well during the breast feeding stage, Greg, infants can get very confused and upset when they\u0027re separated from their mothers.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":495,"aSentId":496},{"question":"Now, Robert, when I -- when you see a trailer like that -- and we have dozens of great movies to choose from, and we choose the one of you wearing mammary glands in \"Meet the Fockers,\" does your heart swell with pride or does part of you think why the hell couldn\u0027t you have done something, you know, a little bit more serious for the great man?","answer":"No, my heart swells with pride.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":509,"aSentId":510},{"question":"What went through your mind and how quickly did you think I\u0027ve got to do something like this?","answer":"Well, we -- I was in Midtown when we were -- when it happened.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":521,"aSentId":522},{"question":"But how did you turn that into what has become not just a -- a New York event, but a -- an international event and one that now generates really big money for New York?","answer":"Well, it -- it happened with a lot of help from a lot of amazing people, as you said, Nelson Mandela and Martin Scorsese and Barry Levinson and Hugh Grant and studios such as Universal Pictures and Warner Brothers and just volunteers and amazing New Yorkers.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":539,"aSentId":540},{"question":"And how could we do something -- what was our creative response to our community and what could we do to just help and give people a new memory to want to come back downtown?","answer":"I mean it\u0027s been -- it\u0027s been, as I say, remarkably successful.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":543,"aSentId":544},{"question":"But, Robert, what do you think about America\u0027s recovery from 9/11 generally?","answer":"Well, I -- downtown has recovered in a lot of ways.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":545,"aSentId":546},{"question":"Well, it -- you want to?","answer":"No, go ahead.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":555,"aSentId":556},{"question":"And, Robert, what would you say?","answer":"the middle class is suffering, as we all know.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":563,"aSentId":564},{"question":"How do you get America\u0027s image, if you like, its reputation, back as the great land of opportunity?","answer":"E NIRO: Well, I think it\u0027s still that.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":580,"aSentId":581},{"question":"Do you -- do you agree with -- do you agree with President Obama\u0027s campaign, this Warren Buffet Rule, that the weal -- the very wealthiest Americans should pay a lot more tax?","answer":"I absolutely do, yes.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":588,"aSentId":589},{"question":"Would you object to -- would you object to paying more?","answer":"Well, I\u0027ll do whatever I have to do, whatever\u0027s fair.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":596,"aSentId":597},{"question":"Astoundingly low?","answer":"Low, yes, very low.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":600,"aSentId":601},{"question":"What do you think of that law in modern America?","answer":"Oh, God, that\u0027s another big question.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":624,"aSentId":625},{"question":"One is, who, to you, is the greatest actor living today, male or female?","answer":"E NIRO: Well, Leonardo DiCaprio is a -- a very serious young actor.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":640,"aSentId":641},{"question":"How -- how is -- how is fatherhood six time around going?","answer":"Oh, it\u0027s great being a -- a parent and -- and my kids are -- I have older kids and younger kids, obviously.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":657,"aSentId":658},{"question":"What do you hope it says about your city, New York?","answer":"I like the idea of the festival not only being just a festival, it\u0027s a -- it\u0027s a cultural thing.","docId":"120416pmt","qSentId":667,"aSentId":668}]